{"id":83126,"title":"Clinical efficacy analysis of the mouth rinsing with pomegranate and chamomile plant extracts in the gingival bleeding reduction.","abstract":"Medicinal plants represent important therapeutic resources to health restoration, including the use of herbal products in the mouth conditions treatment. A randomized controlled clinical trial was performed in order to evaluate the effectiveness of mouth rinse with pomegranate and chamomile plant extracts, against chlorhexidine 0.12% in the gingiva bleeding condition. The mouth rinses with the herbal products were effective for this case, showing thus, antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties similar to that of chlorhexidine 0.12%. ","date":"2014-01-20","categories":"Stomatognathic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24439653","annotations":[{"name":"Anti-inflammatory","weight":0.855989,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anti-inflammatory"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.825112,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Antimicrobial","weight":0.799199,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antimicrobial"},{"name":"Gingiva","weight":0.793903,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gingiva"},{"name":"Pomegranate","weight":0.786823,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pomegranate"},{"name":"Efficacy","weight":0.751777,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Efficacy"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.738087,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Plant","weight":0.73097,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plant"},{"name":"Herbalism","weight":0.70318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herbalism"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.699639,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Randomized controlled trial","weight":0.656858,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Randomized_controlled_trial"},{"name":"Mouth","weight":0.654651,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouth"},{"name":"Redox","weight":0.587145,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Redox"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.572841,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Chlorhexidine","weight":0.37411,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chlorhexidine"},{"name":"Mouthwash","weight":0.238296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouthwash"},{"name":"Herbal","weight":0.107046,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herbal"},{"name":"Order (biology)","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_(biology)"},{"name":"Chamomile","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chamomile"},{"name":"Analytical chemistry","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytical_chemistry"},{"name":"Product (business)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Product_(business)"}]}
